    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-07-08T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-07-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="478"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety Airways/63:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-08T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 8, 1929—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 9—7:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>324. Have vigorously pressed subject of Department’s telegram No. 128, April 30,
                    2 p.m.<note n="70" xml:id="d478fn70">See footnote 55, <ref target="#pg_613">p.
                            613</ref>.</note> French Government now desires to know precise purpose
                    flight, whether scientific, tour, or preparation establishment air line via
                    French possessions. In the latter case delay and possible difficulties
                    anticipated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
